Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Central Park is located approximately 10km south of Dublin City Centre at the base of the Dublin Mountains, and is strategically positioned adjacent to both the M50 Motorway and the N11. With ease of access to the M50 Motorway, Central Park is arguably one of the most accessible office locations in Dublin and is just 30 minutes from Dublin Airport. In addition to the excellent leisure amenities located within Central Park, occupiers can avail of the 10 minute Luas journey to Dundrum Town Centre where there are numerous shops, cafes,restaurants and bars. Dublin City Centre is a further 15 minutes on the Luas where the full city life can be experienced.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are delighted to bring the sixth floor of Building I, Central Park to the market, available by way of sublease under flexible lease terms. The sixth floor is delivered to a Cat A landlord specification and extends to approximately 13,441 sq. ft. (GIA). Tenants can benefit from 10 secure car spaces as well as numerous bicycle spaces.

Extending to approximately 100,000.ft. (GIA) over 8 floors, Building I provides for a state of the art, modern office headquarters. This is a unique opportunity for an occupier to secure a prominent office building within Dublin's most sought after office development. Building I incorporates modern L shaped floor plates and is designed to a very high specification, surpassing the needs and expectations of the most demanding office occupiers.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Mixture of open plan and cellular offices Other

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Situated close to the Luas and the M50, just 10km from Dublin’s City Centre, with easy access to the City Centre and the Wicklow countryside. Sandyford is serviced by a major intersection of the M50 motorway which provides an approximate 30-minute route to the airport. It also offers a quick path around Dublin towards Belfast and the North and is the starting point for journeys to the midlands, Limerick and Galway. The N11 dual carriageway that runs by Sandyford offers straightforward north and south-bound access to and from the City Centre. It also features a much-improved Quality Bus Corridor (QBC) that provides public transport links to the City, the South, and other surrounding areas. Also, on your doorstep is the Aircoach to Dublin Airport via the City Centre. Situated in close proximity to a rich array of recreational and Leisure amenities.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The 3rd floor provides 23,800 sq.ft of office space. The design features a high degree of flexibility enabling the optimum space solutions for different levels of corporate occupier, and the high-spec fit-out incorporates the latest in environmental technologies. The 3rd floor also includes 23 underground car spaces. The current tenants within the building include Service Source, Regus Dublin, GMI research and Mars Ireland. The 3rd floor is fully fitted with a mixture of open floor plan space, cellular offices and canteen space. Amenities within the building include Café/Restaurant  (La Dolce Vita), Landscaped Plaza and underground parking. Sandyford Luas stop, Aircoach to Dublin Airport Stop and M50 are all within close proximity. Beacon South Quarter is situated in close proximity which provides convenience store and dining options such as Dunnes, Freshi, Zambrero, Starbucks, Chopped Sandyford and Pizza Hut.

The Loft is a new premium office opportunity situated in the heart of Dundrum’s Pembroke District, South Dublin’s exciting dining, events and leisure quarter. The Loft is an ideal space for emerging and established companies, for creativity, collaboration and socialising.

Offering 1,050 sq m of premium office space, The Loft boasts a large open-plan workspace, and a private roof terrace with views across Dublin city and the Dublin mountains.

Located just 15 minutes on public transport from the centre of Dublin, The Loft is positioned in the heart of Dundrum Town Centre – Ireland’s premier retail and leisure destination.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Located on Merrion Road in the heart of Dublin's prestigious Dublin 4, the Seamark Building has a whole host of amenities within easy reach. Ballsbridge, one of Dublin's most charming suburbs, is a short stroll away. It's bustling village atmosphere as well as its many restaurants, cafés and pubs make it an attractive place to visit. Close by you will also find the Aviva Stadium and the RDS. 

Meanwhile, local shopping centres, The Merrion Centre, Frascati Shopping Centre & Blackrock Shopping Centre provide an array of boutiques, shops, cafes and supermarkets to choose from. Right on your doorstep are some of Dublin's best coastline stretches, with spectacular views across the bay to Howth. Just a stone's throw from the campus Sandymount Beach offers superb opportunities to get into the great outdoors with its long promenade and cycle track.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Seamark Building is part of Ireland's first sustainable, mixed-use campus. Designed with versatility and adaptability in mind, it can facilitate two fully independent office blocks with their own identity or a standalone Headquarter building. The building provides an A3 BER rating and a LEED Platinum building certificate. 

Providing 16,940 sq metres of Grade A Office Accommodation over eight floors, the Seamark Building is the most prominent, commandingand impressive block within Elmpark Green. 

Located on Merrion Road in the heart of Dublin's prestigious Dublin 4, the Seamark Building has a whole host of amenities within easy reach. Ballsbridge, one of Dublin's most charming suburbs, is a short stroll away. It's bustling village atmosphere as well as its many restaurants, cafés and pubs make it an attractive place to visit. Close by you will also find the Aviva Stadium and the RDS. 

Meanwhile, local shopping centres, The Merrion Centre, Frascati Shopping Centre & Blackrock Shopping Centre provide an array of boutiques, shops, cafes and supermarkets to choose from. Right on your doorstep are some of Dublin's best coastline stretches, with spectacular views across the bay to Howth. Just a stone's throw from the campus Sandymount Beach offers superb opportunities to get into the great outdoors with its long promenade and cycle track.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Airfield House is located on the edge of Donnybrook next to the Stillorgan Road, one of the arterial routes into the city centre. With numerous public transport options nearby such as a Dublin Bus station and Sydney Parade DART station. 



Being located in such an amenity rich location provides occupants with many recreational, sport, academic and residential options nearby. University College Dublin and Elm Park Golf Club can be accessed within the immediate vicinity. Donnybrook village is a prime location with many different amenities, it is also home to many restaurants and hotels such as Marco Pierre White, Mao, Radisson Blue St Helen’s and the Herbert Park Hotel. Cafés in the area include Insomnia, Donnybrook fair and Café Nero all of which are within walking distance. 



Many international companies such as Paddy Power and Ericsson have chosen Donnybrook as the home to their European location. Neighbouring areas include Ballsbridge, Ranelagh and Clonskeagh.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Airfield House is an own door, 3 storey period office building. The property has been refurbished back to a high standard and the provision of a modern extension to the rear of the property, provide a good mix of old and new. Some of the main period features include its grand boardrooms and high ceilings which also provide a flurry of natural light.  The property has one internal passenger lift that provides access to all floors.
CBRE are delighted to be marketing Hume House in Dublin 4. Planning has been granted to develop approximately 154,000 sq ft of prime Grade A office accommodation.

CBRE are delighted to bring to the market this Fully-Fitted sublease in 3 Shelbourne Buildings in the heart of Ballsbridge. The available space is located on the 3rd floor and extends to c. 8,963 sq.ft. of modern Grade A specification office space. A sub-tenant here will also enjoy the benefit of an impressive 7 car spaces with the sublease, which is far in excess of the norm.

Located off Shelbourne road the building is extremely well located in relation to access to public transport, namely the dart at Landsdowne Road and the QBC on Merrion Road. Being in the heart of Ballsbridge occupiers benefit from vast amenities and lunchtime destinations on their doorstep making this a very desirable address.

CBRE are delighted to be marketing 2 Grand Parade,the redevelopment of one of Dublin’s most iconic office buildings. Hines Ireland have planning for the refurbishment and extension of the existing building consisting of c.103,000 sq ft. 

Two Grand Parade is conveniently located along the Grand Canal in Dublin 6 adjacent to the Charlemont LUAS stop and is within walking distance to St. Stephens Green.Originally constructed in 1962, the property is in a unique city centre setting with unrivalled landscaped gardens. 

The building has been designed to LEED Gold standards and Hines Ireland is also exploring WELL Certification.

Iveagh Court presents a unique opportunity to secure prominent office space with an exclusive business address in the leafy surrounds of Dublin 2. Situated on Harcourt Road, this newly refurbished property offers 36 sq m of prime office accommodation within striking distance of St. Stephen’s Green and Grafton Street. 

Step out of Iveagh Court and the colour and character of the city greets you with an abundance of shops and eateries waiting to cater for every appetite. Restaurants, cafes and gyms are all but a short stroll from the hustle and bustle of Harcourt Road. The renowned retail quarter that is Grafton Street is only 10 minutes away on foot and offers an array of lunchtime and recreational opportunities to explore.

Exceptional amenities and transport links add to the appeal of Iveagh Court. Superbly positioned at the gateway to the Central Business District from South Dublin City. Adjacent to the Harcourt Luas station providing professionals with easy access to St. Stephen’s Green, Dundrum and Sandyford. Walk to the beautiful Iveagh Gardens in only five minutes. Experience all the sights and sounds of Grafton Street in 10 minutes.

Iveagh Court provides an excellent easily accessible office opportunity in the heart of Dublin’s Central Business District. The property benefits from a high specification refurbished reception area. Commercial occupiers in the immediate vicinity include Bloomberg, EY, Investec & Merill Lynch.

Transport is well catered for in the area with the LUAS Green Line & LUAS cross City located on Harcourt Street. The QBC is located on Leeson Street & St. Stephen’s Green serving virtually every area of the city. Dublinbikes are also located on our doorstep.

Situated at the top of Harcourt Street, Iveagh Court is ideally located in the heart of Dublin 2. The property is positioned within walking distance of St. Stephen’s Green & Grafton Street, both of which provide a host of restaurants, cafés, bars, gyms and high street retailers.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
57 Adelaide has an unrivalled presence in Georgian Dublin. Situated at the junction of Lower Leeson Street and Adelaide Road, the property commands an excellent profile on one of the main arterial routes into the City Centre. Lower Leeson Street is ideally located within walking distance of Grafton Street, St. Stephen’s Green, Merrion Square and Trinity College. 

The property is within close proximity to the DART and LUAS Green Line as well as being serviced by multiple Dublin Bus
Routes along Lower Leeson Street. The surrounding area forms part of the Central Business District and is a popular location for commercial activity.
Adjoining professional and corporate occupiers include OPW, Deloitte accountants, Arthur Cox Solicitors and ESB. Occupiers in 57 Adelaide can enjoy the perfect work- life balance with bars, restaurants, gyms and many other amenities all within a short walk.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
57 Adelaide has been recently refurbished to a high standard and provides the elegance of a Georgian building to the front while catering for today’s modern office needs with a refurbished office block to the rear. The entire is available to let under a new lease or on a floor by floor basis providing an occupier with a unique office opportunity in Dublin 2. 



The Georgian building extends to approx.3,857 sq ft and has retained many of its original decorative features. The modern building is now fully refurbished and interconnects with the Georgian on the ground floor and extends to approximately 17,513 sq ft over four floors. Floorplates in the modern office block range in size from c. 2,423 sq. ft to 6,106 sq. ft.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
One Park place is located on Hatch Street Upper, in the heart Dublin’s Central Business District. With unrivalled views of the Iveagh Gardens and its proximity to Ireland’s most popular retail destination, Grafton Street, One Park Place provides its occupiers with easy access to a large selection to retail, dining and leisure amenities among second to none transport links.

Dining options near One Park Place include Sophie’s, The Grayson and The Odeon whilst café’s such as Starbucks, The Art of Coffee and Morton’s are in the immediate vicinity. Leisure amenities located near One Park Place include St. Stephens Green, The National Concert Hall, Dublin’s most popular restaurants and neighbouring hotels such as The Shelbourne, The Dean and The Hilton. 

This unique location has proven to be extremely popular with large multinational companies such as Dropbox, Bank of America, Arthur Cox, Deloitte and the IDA establishing themselves here.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Forming part of one of Dublin's most premier commercial developments, One Park Place provides tenants with a location in the heart of Dublin's Central Business District and office space designed to the highest of standards. Available by way of sublease, the second and third floor comprising 25,116 sq. ft. and 29,220 sq. ft. come with a previous tenant fit out providing a plug-and-play opportunity. With some of the best specification to include raised access floors, suspended ceilings and LED lighting, this space is in line with some of the best offices in Dublin.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Location is everything and set between St Stephens Green and the emerging Camden Quarter, The Greenside Building provides an occupier all the city has to offer.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Greenside Building, due for completion in 2023, will feature touch-free access control devices, automated opening doors, anti-bacterial surfaces, an upgraded air-quality filtration systems, integrated smartphone technology for lift functionality, touch-free security turnstiles, occupancy sensors to offices and changing rooms, touch-free operation of sanitary fittings and temperature-check sensors in the reception lobby. The building occupies a prime location just 100m from the southwest corner of St Stephen’s Green. 

The Greenside Building was designed by architect Paschal Mahoney. It will feature a glazed facade wrapped in a diagonal brise-soleil with the resulting diamond pattern serving to create the building’s distinctive appearance. The building will offer efficient floor plates and flexibility from 3,000sq ft to 5,000sq ft. Occupier requirements will be accommodated from 3,000sq ft to 40,348sq ft.



The Greenside Building has been designed to meet the latest environmental, nZEB (nearly zero energy building), sustainability and digital connectivity standards. The building will carry a BER rating of A3 and is being designed to achieve LEED Gold certification, Wiredscore Gold, and a Well building Gold standard. In line with these great accreditations, this office accommodation will be delivered to the highest specification and be complemented by facilities that include secure bicycle parking and locker-room, changing and shower facilities.

25 St Stephens Green is located in Dublin's most sought after established business address providing a unique office opportunity in the heart of Dublin 2. The property is located to the north side of Stephen’s Green between Kildare St and Dawson Street. The immediate area has attracted Global leading companies which include KPMG, Intercom, Standard Life, AerCap, Davy and many more. 

The building benefits from excellent transport links including DART and LUAS connecting you throughout Dublin. Numerous Dublin bus routes are available within close proximity of the office space. There is a host of shops, cafés and restaurants all within the immediate area. 

25 St Stephens Green consists of a 6-storey office building extending to approximately 752 sq. m (8,092 sq. ft).  Floorplates range in size from c. 90 sq. m (971 sq. ft) to 158.3 sq. m (1,703 sq. ft). The floors offer exceptional views overlooking St. Stephens Green. The building has recently undergone an internal refurbishment to include new entrance and an upgraded foyer/reception area.  Each floor offers open plan office accommodation with new carpet tile flooring, new LED lighting, suspended ceilings, kitchenettes and refurbished toilet accommodation.  

The property is available on flexible lease terms in its entirety on a floor by floor basis.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The Eight Building is a newly designed Grade A office development in the heart of Dublin 8’s distinctive Newmarket Square. This central and well-established area has long been at the forefront of the history of Dublin City. The deep- rooted locality, originally known as the centre of craft distilling and brewing in Dublin, has in recent years been transformed to one of the City’s most up and coming regenerated Quarters. 

Newmarket Square has seen major transformation in recent years to include the newly designed Aloft Hotel, student accommodation catering for approximately 700+ bedrooms and a range of retail and recreational amenities. This vibrant district is filled with culture and provides an array of coffee shops, bars & restaurants all within easy reach. Also known as Dublin’s premier design district being home to NCAD which is Ireland’s largest and oldest art and design college.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Eight Building is a Grade A office situated in Newmarket Square, Dublin 8. This modern office comprises of over 75,000 sq. ft (NIA) of open-plan office space across five floors above basement. Floor plates range from 3000 sq. ft to 16,000 sq ft and are capable of accommodating a single tenancy or a floor split. The Eight building boasts approx. 3,500 sq. ft of terrace space across three floors. 

There are 18 car spaces and a further 96 bicycle spaces within the basement. There are also 2 electric car charging ports located in the basement. Tenants have 8 showers located on the ground floor and 3x15 person passenger lifts servicing the building. Specification includes; 2.9 Metre Floor to Ceiling height, 1:8 sq. m occupancy ratio, LED Lighting and a dedicated comms intake room in the basement.

124 St Stephens Green presents a unique opportunity for an occupier to occupy fitted, flexible office accommodation in a prestigious corporate headquarters. Home to Indeed, the building has been remodelled and designed to provide for a modern working environment exceeding the needs of todays office occupiers.  



Located in Dublin's most sought after established business address, the area has attracted Global leading companies which include KPMG, Intercom, Standard Life, AerCap, Davy and many more. 



The second floor extends to approximately 17,242 sq. ft (NIA). The third floor extends to approximately 17,240 sq. ft (NIA). The fifth floor extends to approximately 14,372 sq. ft (NIA) and each floor will be handed over with the benefit of newly completed refurbishment works throughout. The tenant will have the benefit of an existing fit-out providing a turn-key “plug and play” solution. The floor plate has been designed to provide optimum flexibility and can be easily adapted to suit a variety of occupier needs. The flexible layout cleverly facilitates a simultaneous flow of board meetings, management briefings, breakouts and day to day working, all in the surroundings of natural daylight.

Park West Business Campus comprises approximately 92 acres providing high-specification offices and local amenities. The office accommodation can cater for a range of sizes for small to medium/ large companies. The campus is located south west of the city, adjacent to the Naas Road and adjoining the M50 motorway. Park West is easily accessible by train and is a 25 minute commute from the City Centre. Additional facilities within the development include -  O`Brien`s Sandwich Bar, SPAR convenience store, Giraffe Childcare and Jackie Skelly fitness centre.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Park West Office Available To Let

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Park West Business Campus comprises approximately 92 acres providing high-specification offices and local amenities. The office accommodation can cater for a range of sizes for small to medium/ large companies.

The campus is located south west of the city, adjacent to the Naas Road and adjoining the M50 motorway. Park West is easily accessible by train and is a 25 minute commute from the City Centre.


Additional facilities within the development include -  O`Brien`s Sandwich Bar, SPAR convenience store, Giraffe Childcare and Jackie Skelly fitness centre.

Park West Business Campus comprises approximately 92 acres providing high-specification offices and local amenities. The office accommodation can cater for a range of sizes for small to medium/ large companies.

The campus is located south west of the city, adjacent to the Naas Road and adjoining the M50 motorway. Park West is easily accessible by train and is a 25 minute commute from the City Centre.

Additional facilities within the development include -  O`Brien`s Sandwich Bar, SPAR convenience store, Giraffe Childcare and Jackie Skelly fitness centre.

One Le Pole Square is in the heart of the City, directly adjacent to Dublin Castle and within 5 minutes of Grafton St and St Stephens Green. The site is ideally located within walking distance of the centre of the city, adjacent to transport corridors, near tourism and heritage buildings and in an area which is currently undergoing regeneration. 

The regeneration of this site forms the basis of a significant urban renewal scheme in one of the most archaeologically sensitive areas of Dublin’s medieval city. A new pedestrian street will link Chancery Lane and Ship Street Great; on this route a new civic square will be created over the remains of 7th-century St. Michael Le Pole church. The site is one of the most prominent locations of the new urban quarter of Dublin Castle on which a landmark building of the highest architectural quality is considered necessary. The project creates an historic context, creating a sense of place by adapting to the context and urban pattern.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: x 7 and 1 Services Lift Passenger Lifts

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Hanover Quay is arguably the best address in Dublin's South Docklands. It forms the northern boundary of the Grand Canal Dock, one of the largest in Europe. All of its buildings have been completed within the last 15 years and provide a modern mix of offices, residential and leisure uses.  As you look south towards the Dublin Mountains, your neighbours will include Accenture, Airbnb, Matheson and State Street to name but a few.

It is one of Dublin's most trendy and exciting places to work.

With two high quality hotels trading within 5 minutes walk, as well as a wide selection of cafes, restaurants and convenience shops the area has  everything occupiers desire nearby.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
5 Hanover Quay is a striking new development in the heart of Dublin’s South Docks and the entire building extends to approximately 161,300 sq ft in total. Located in the heart of Dublin’s CBD, 5 Hanover Quay’s has already attracted leading occupiers which include DocuSign and Aptive whilst neighbouring tenants include some of the biggest companies in the world; Google, Airbnb, HSBC, State Street, Accenture, Facebook, TripAdvisor and many more.



The property delivers fully fitted accommodation which provides a turn-key solution for occupiers. The property is laid out to provide a mixture of open plan and cellular offices and has the added benefit of natural light throughout. This layout flexibility provides potential for the space to be easily adapted to suit a variety of occupier needs.



The first floor extends to 24,401 sq ft and has the benefit of 5 secure basement car spaces.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The location is one of the most connected in the city with the LUAS, numerous Dublin Bus Routes passing within minutes of the property and within a short walk to the nearest Dart station.

South William Street is the city centre’s fastest-growing commercial locations with an array of bars, cafés and restaurants.

The quality of the location is already underpinned by the standard of occupiers who have already chose to locate their business within the surrounding area.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The mid terraced building provides occupiers with the opportunity to secure fitted premium office space extending to c. 2,340 sq. ft.

The penthouse floor provides a mixture of open plan, meeting rooms and individual offices. 

The building is finished to a modern standard with the common areas recently refurbished. The highly efficient floor plates offer a large open plan space providing a bright and spacious working environment. 

This opportunity will appeal to occupiers across a range of industries.

The first and second floor office suites provide occupiers with the opportunity to secure premium fitted office space in Dublin’s most dynamic business quarter. CBRE are delighted to offer approximately 22,065 sq. ft. of fitted office accommodation which includes a canteen, reception area, board room, meeting rooms, photocopying/filling room and managers office. The space is available immediately and a viewing of the space is highly recommended.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: First & Second Floor, Central Quay, Sir John Rogerson’s Quay, Dublin 2

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The Sorting Office is located at the junction of Cardiff Lane and Hanover Street, in the heart of the thriving south docks in Dublin's CBD. The area is surrounded by numerous restaurants, pubs, the Grand Canal Theatre, hotels, leisure and recreational amenities. The immediate area is readily accessible to numerous transport modes. Dublin Bus, the DART and LUAS all provide easy access for staff coming from any area of the city. Dublin Airport is only a 20-minute drive and the M50 is easily accessible through the port tunnel. Dublin bike stations also surround the property.

This is an ideal hub for organisations seeking a European Base. Over recent years the Grand Canal / South Docklands area has been reinvented, delivering some of the most prestigious commercial buildings Dublin has to offer.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Sorting Office delivers approximately 213,000 sq. ft of dynamic Grade A office space to Dublin’s South Docklands. The Sorting Office has been designed with occupiers in mind, allowing total flexibility of the space. The property is available immediately for a tenant fit out and is located over 8 floors in the heart of Dublin’s South Docklands. 



The basement consists of 24 car parking spaces, 318 secure bike spaces, changing and locker facilities, 24 showers and storage space. The ground floor benefits from an impressive double height reception area with contactless security barriers leading to a large full height atrium/collaboration space, office space and 8 destination controlled lifts to the upper floors. The upper floors are designed with flexibility in mind and have wrap around floor to ceiling glazing centred around a light filled atrium.

CBRE are delighted to bring the second floor in 2 Windmill Lane to the market by way of a short-term sub lease likely to be within 3-5 years.



The second floor extends to approximately 13,117 sq ft (NIA) and will be delivered fitted to provide for a modern working environment exceeding the needs of today's office occupiers.



2 Windmill Lane presents a unique opportunity for an occupier to occupy the last remaining floor in a prestigious corporate headquarters. The building has been designed to incorporate best international design standards throughout and achieve Building Energy A3 Rating, LEED Gold classification and a Platinum Wired Score.



2 Windmill Lane is located within the Windmill Quarter of SOBO where the Dublin Docklands, IFSC and City Centre converge. Owned by Hibernia REIT plc, this visionary business area is master planned to provide everything that a modern company needs. 

The area has attracted Global leading companies which include Zalando, Udemy, Asana, Pluralsight and many more.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Flexible Office Space To Let D2

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Designed to optimise space, flexibility and views with full height glazing maximising natural daylight, the scheme comprises approx. 80,000 sq. ft. It offers two distinct but connected buildings; an upgraded and converted Victorian warehouse structure to the front that will be refurbished to the highest standard of modern offices. Complimenting this, a highly efficient, modern 6 storey office block will be created at the southern end of the property overlooking Whitaker Square. 

An attractive landscaped and exclusively pedestrianised zone leading from the quay side will provide unrivaled synergy between the two buildings and create an ambient outdoor environment. 

The building has been designed to meet the highest global standards in design and sustainability credentials to include NZEB and LEED Platinum standards and WELL Gold enabled. 

Constructed in the 1890's this original warehouse has continuously evolved over the last 127 years and is now set to become an inspirational work space for the future.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Ease of access is one of the many reasons why Dublin’s North Quays has become such a successful business district. Buses and trams pass every few minutes, linking the city centre and train stations. The nearby East Link Bridge provides a direct route to the city’s southside. The M50 and Port Tunnel are close by, making all parts of Ireland easy to reach by road, and Dublin International Airport is just 15 minutes away. There are also numerous Dublin Bike stations, and ample car parking spaces.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Stretching skyward, its appearance of being suspended in mid-air, its visibility on the Dublin skyline, the revolutionary design and construction techniques, its location, the panoramic views, the quality of the space, its prestige... the EXO is truly bringing statement offices to extraordinary new heights.17 storeys of elegance, beauty and strength, elevated to allow easy movement around it, the EXO Building presents an exciting opportunity like no other in Dublin. The Exo Building has been designed to target a building energy rating of A3 and LEED Gold certification.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: The Exo - One Building Above All

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: The Docklands comprises of a mix of international companies, multiple high-end residential options and an eclectic range of restaurants, bars and casual coffee operators. It is this balance of a living and working environment which makes the Docklands sought after office location for world leading companies with No. 3 Dublin Landings located at its core.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
No. 3 Dublin Landings has been built with an emphasis on sustainability and energy efficiency, underwritten by LEED accreditation, ensuring occupiers can minimise both both operational costs and environmental impact. Further contributing to sustainability and efficency, No. 3 Dublin Landings has been designed to the highest standard, with premium finishes throughout. This striking office HQ extends to over 119,000 sq ft in the heart of the Dublin Docklands.



At the epicentre of Dublin’s thriving Docklands, No. 3 forms part of the established Dublin Landings Scheme which is a mixed use development extending to over 1 million sq ft (92,900 sq m) anchored by the National Treasury Management Agency of Ireland (NTMA) and other Government agencies. Dublin Landings offers over 270 high-end residential apartments, a range of eateries, leisure offerings and a boutique hotel.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Number One Georges Quay Plaza forms part of the Georges Quay office development which commands strategic location in the heart of the city centre.

The location is one of the most connected in the city with DART, LUAS and numerous Dublin Bus Routes passing within minutes of the property. The development’s location on the south side of the River Liffey enjoys ease of access from all parts of the city and beyond. The quality of the location is already underpinned by the quality of occupiers who have already chose to locate their business within the development which include The Office of Public Works (OPW) Ulster Bank, PepsiCo, Fidelity and WeWork amongst others.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The second floor suite of One Georges Quay Plaza is fitted to the highest specification throughout and extends to approximately Size 7,095 sq. ft.

Upon arrival, visitors are greeted by a welcoming reception area with direct boardroom access. The main floor plate provides a mixture of open plan, meeting rooms and individual offices. In addition, the accommodation has the added benefit of a dedicated comms room and canteen space. 

The accommodation is presented in a bright and modern condition throughout and will appeal to occupiers across a range of industries. The second floor suite also enjoys use of the on site Amenity Zone which includes:

- 12 high quality shower rooms

- 200 individual storage lockers

- Drying facilities

- 200 secure bicycle parking spaces

The specification comprises the following in summary:

- Raised access floors

- Carpet floor covering 

- Plastered and painted walls

- Glazed internal partitioning system 

- Suspended Ceiling 

- LED Lighting

- Air conditioning 

- Dedicated comms room 

- Canteen Area 

- 6 secure car parking spaces

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Georges Quay House is located by Dublin’s River Liffey, providing a highly accessible location with Numerous modes of transport within walking distance.

-Dublin bikes – 3 minutes-DART - 4 minutes-Bus - 4 minutes-Luas – 5 minutes

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
George’s Quay House is a 5-storey modern office building designed to the highest standards. It provides bright office accommodation with a large light filled internal atrium. George’s Quay House has been designed and constructed to the highest of standards providing efficient and modern office accommodation and is home to Fidelity International, Citizens Information Board and WeWork. Located in one of Dublin’s most accessible locations, the Georges Quay office complex has attracted many large companies such as Vanguard, First Derivatives and Ulster Bank. 

The first floor extends to 22,139 sq. ft. and comes fully fitted. This space provides a modern fit-out and comes available by sublease on a flexible lease term. This floor provides occupiers with a ready-to-go or “plug and play” option. The highly efficient floor plates and fit-out adapts to occupiers from various sectors and the bright central atrium brings plenty of natural light across the entire floor.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Dockline will deliver a fully refurbished 80,000 sq ft HQ office building in the heart of the IFSC. The thriving location boasts excellent connectivity with the Red Luas line running along Mayor Street, the nearest stop is approximately 100m east of the subject property. Connolly DART/Rail Station and the Red Line Luas interchange are located within 3 minutes’ walk of the property which provides unparalled connectivity to all parts of the city and beyond. The direct vicinity boasts an excellent mix of amenities consisting of a number of
pubs, restaurants and cafes. The nearby CHQ building is home to Starbucks, ELY Bar & Grill, Chopped, J2 Sushi and Tea and Freshii.
The local area is already home to leading occupiers which include Citi Bank, BNP Paribas, A&L Goodbody, KPMG, Hubspot, Salesforce and PWC to name but a few.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Dockline is accessed via a high profile entrance onto Mayor Street. Design features include an expansive double height reception with views directly onto an internal landscaped courtyard, a unique oasis in a city location. The building has been designed with maximum flexibility throughout with regular floorplate configuration and abundant natural light throughout. The building benefits from two lift cores and has generous toilet allocation on every level. The building welfare facilities have been designed to clubhouse standard with male and female showers, a drying room and generous locker allocation all provided at basement level. There are 59 secure basement car spaces and 196 bicycle spaces.

Jervis House is a modern office block located in the heart of Dublin's City Centre. The building is ideally located within walking distance of O'Connell Street, Temple Bar and located opposite Jervis Street Shopping Centre. Occupiers here have the benefit of numerous Bus Routes along the Quays and O'Connell Street as well as having the Luas on it's door step connecting to the DART.The available space has recently been refurbished to the highest standards and boasts great natural light as well as a private decking area. The space has been delivered with the following specification in place;

Raised Access Floors , Suspended Ceilings, New Carpeting, New Tea Station, New Decking, New LED Lighting, Air ConditioningLift, Ample Car Parking

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: 6 George's Dock is also located in one of the most highly connected office locations in Ireland and has unrivalled connectivity to local, national and international transport modes including LUAS, Dublin Bikes, DART and Dublin Bus which are all located within a five minute walk. Dublin Airport is also very accessible located just 25 minutes away.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 6 George's Dock, IFSC is a building situated in the epicentre of Dublin's Premier Financial Business District. CBRE are delighted to offer the part ground floor 5,033 sq ft (467 sqm) to the market under sublease or assignment. The office has raised access floor, carpet floor covering, suspended ceilings and air conditioning. This iconic building has a host of occupier amenities including generous floor to ceiling heights, internal passenger lifts, 6 car spaces, previous tenant fitout and an internal shower. 6 George's Dock is also located in one of the most highly connected office locations in Ireland and has unrivalled connectivity to local, national and international transport modes including LUAS, Dublin Bikes, DART and Dublin Bus which are all located within a five minute walk. Dublin Airport is also very accessible located just 25 minutes away.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
3 Harbourmaster place provides unrivalled connectivity and accessibility for its tenants with Connolly Train & Luas Station, Numerous Dublin Bus stops, Busáras Central Station, Dublin Bikes and the Marlborough Luas Stop all on your doorstep. 

This central location is ideally positioned near a host of amenities. Tenants can enjoy many different choices of restaurants and cafes on Talbot Street and the North Dock or go shopping at some of Dublin’s busiest retail destinations such as O’Connell Street, Henry Street or Shopping Centres such as the Ilac or Jervis, all located within walking distance.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The available penthouse unit at 3 Harbourmaster Place extends to 5,300 sq. ft and comes as part of a split of the top floor. This grade A office space comes in a high specification and benefits from a recent refurbishment of the lobby and toilets. The specification includes raised access floors, air conditioning, carpets, showers, CAT 6 cabling, suspended ceilings and a tea station. 



The space also has the benefit of a previous tenant fit-out representing significant savings on capital expenditure for an incoming tenant.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: The International Financial Services Centre (IFSC) is home to many of the world's leading multinational companies. Originally, the IFSC was a destination for banks and financial institutions however today it is home to all types of industries. Companies such as BNP Paribas, Sumitomo Bank, KPMG, Citibank, SMBC Aviation Capital, Wells Fargo and HubSpot have all located their headquarters in the IFSC.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 5 Harbourmaster Place is a 3-storey office building, constructed over the southern side of the existing station concourse and former railway arches at ground level, with own door access from Harbourmaster Place, within the IFSC northern precinct. The building consists of a newly decorated and light filled ground floor entrance lobby with 2 x 8-person passenger lifts and a circulation staircase to all levels. The second floor has been totally refurbished to a high standard which is further enhanced by the regular shaped floor plate which extends to approximately 12,250 sq. ft. and offers great flexibility to an incoming occupier. With glazing on all aspects, this provides excellent natural light into the working environment.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Modern Office to Let in Dublin's Most Accessible Location

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Telephone House is located on the north end of Marlborough Street and west of Dublin’s iconic O’Connell Street. This highly popular tourist destination is home to a host of amenities and high profile occupiers, some of these include the Irish life centre, Valuation Office, GPO and An Board Pleanala.
The property is located amongst some of Dublin’s best retail districts, Henry street which is home to the Jervis Centre and the Ilac centre. One of the great benefits of Telephone House is the number of transport links in the surrounding and immediate areas, the Luas Tram is approximately 50m away, Tara Street dart station is 850m away and the area is well served by Dublin Bus.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Telephone House comprises a nine story over basement prime office building in Dublin’s city centre, extending to approximately 80,773 sq ft with typical floor plates ranging around 9,500 sq ft. The property benefits from kitchenettes and bathroom facilities on each floor with a grand reception, main canteen area and internal passenger lifts on the ground floor. The property benefits from high ceilings with typical floor to ceiling heights ranging between 2.97 and 4.35m. Floor plates are mainly open plan making them highly customisable for an incoming tenant.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: To Let by Sub-Let / Assignment - Telephone House

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Eastpoint Business Park is Irelands most prestigious and successful business campus. It comes as no surprise that Eastpoint is home to companies such as Oracle, Activision, Google and British Airways that have chosen Ireland as their European hub. The park is strategically located a short distance from the CBD and IFSC. The park also benefits from ease of access to the Dublin port tunnel and the M50. Eastpoint Business Park provides occupants with a host of tenant amenities which include Insomnia, Blockburger, Links Childcare Creche and SPOORSE Dry Cleaning.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The available accommodation comprises one floor extending to approximately 7,700 sq. ft in Block P1 of Eastpoint Business Park, the first floor is available by way of assignment from IQVIA. Block P1 occupies a prominent position in Dublin’s only central business park. This grade A office space comes with an existing tenant fit-out and very flexible terms. The office is mainly open plan with meeting rooms, breakout spaces and cellular office space. Floor to ceiling glazing also provide a flurry of bright and natural light, which really give the space a welcoming feel.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Office to Let by way of Assignment

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Male and Female on each floor Toilets

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Eastpoint Business Park is Irelands most prestigious and successful business campuses. The park is strategically located a short distance from the city centre and IFSC. The park also benefits from ease of access to the Dublin port tunnel and M50. Eastpoint Business Park provides occupants with a different setting to that of the city centre with it’s landscaped gardens and waterfront walks whilst still being situated next to Dublin’s Central Business District. It comes with no surprise that some of the world’s largest companies such as Google, Oracle, Datalex and British Airways have chosen Eastpoint Business Park as their Irish hub.



Strategically positioned on the edge of Dublin’s city centre, Eastpoint Business Park is in the immediate vicinity of Clontarf DART Station. DART Services connect commuters directly to Connolly Station, which is the main station in connecting transport in the capital with numerous Dublin Bus routes, Bus Áras, and Luas lines immediately accessible. Eastpoint also benefits from its own private shuttle bus service which operates exclusively for occupants of the business park. This private service connects people to Clontarf and Dublin’s Docklands, from there provides access to any number of the many transport services mentioned above.
Occupants can also easily access both the M50 and M1, two of Dublin’s main motorway’s which provide access to all of Ireland, Dublin Airport can also be easily accessed via the Port Tunnel.
